09/08/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro's National Council for Co-operation with the International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia will convene this week, Council Chairman Rasim Ljajic said Sunday (8 August).
Ljajic, who is also Serbia-Montenegro's human rights minister, said the session would most likely take place Wednesday.
It will focus on requests by relatives of Hague indictees for material and financial help as well as on prosecutors' demands for access to documentation, Ljajic said.
(Tanjug, Beta - 08/08/04)
